The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 13: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (IRDA) has asked life insurers to provide scrip-wise details of their investments. According to the guideline, insurance companies are required to disclose details of their investments in both mandated and non-mandated scrips so that their solvency margin can be determined.                             
	 Mumbai, March 13: The RBI has rejected all the bids for Rs 12,000-crore government bonds to stem a runaway rise in bond yields, an official release said.                            
	 Mumbai, March 13: The directors of Hirco Plc, an investment vehicle of the Hiranandani group, have threatened to resign from the board if any resolutions proposed by hedge fund Laxey Partners is approved in the upcoming extra-ordinary general meeting.                            
	 Mumbai, March 13: Sebi chairman C.B. Bhave said the market regulator was planning fundamental reforms for the mutual fund industry. He said the recent liquidity crisis faced by mutual funds was over.                            
	 Calcutta, March 13: Vibgyor Vehicles plans to invest about Rs 660 crore over the next two years to boost its presence in the two-wheeler market. The firm will introduce a 125cc bike in May and a utility vehicle before the festive season.                                                                                                                           
